  "Brown the beef kidney on both sides for 2 minutes per side in 3 tablespoons of olive oil. Add 1 cup of all-purpose flour and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly to thicken the sauce. Add 1 cup of red wine and 2 cups of beef stock, stirring to combine. Bring the sauce to a boil and then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in 2 tablespoons of tomato paste and 2 ounces of tempering chocolate until melted and smooth. Season the sauce with 1 teaspoon of salt and 1 teaspoon of black pepper. Stir in 4 whole eggs and cook for 1 minute, until the sauce is thick and creamy. Add 1 cup of crumbled feta cheese to the sauce and stir until combined. Combine the cooked pasta and the sauce, stirring to combine. Transfer the pasta to a large casserole dish and top with chopped parsley. Dot the top of the pasta with 2 tablespoons of butter. Bake the pasta in a preheated oven at 375°F for 20 minutes, until the top is golden brown and the sauce is bubbly. Serve the pasta hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired.": ".$prepTimeMin",
